#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/era.rst:8
msgid ""
"dm-era is a target that behaves similar to the linear target.  In addition "
"it keeps track of which blocks were written within a user defined period of "
"time called an 'era'.  Each era target instance maintains the current era as "
"a monotonically increasing 32-bit counter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/era.rst:14
msgid ""
"Use cases include tracking changed blocks for backup software, and partially "
"invalidating the contents of a cache to restore cache coherency after "
"rolling back a vendor snapshot."
msgstr ""

